{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Apologise for the Balfour Declaration and fund the teaching of its legacy",
        "additional_details": "We believe Britain\u2019s policies from 1917-1948 shaped events that led to the displacement of Palestinians and left a legacy still felt today. Many MPs, legal experts and historians have argued that Britain failed to uphold the rights of the Palestinian population. A formal apology could offer symbolic justice, while investment in education - both in the UK and internationally- could ensure this history is accurately taught, understood, and not forgotten by future generations.",
        "background": "We ask the Government to issue a formal apology for the Balfour Declaration and Britain\u2019s actions in Mandate-era Palestine, and to commit to funding educational initiatives that acknowledge this history. This should include public resources and curriculum support reflecting Britain\u2019s role.",
